Let me explain what a matcher is and then suggest we update the original hook to include `"matcher": "*"`.

A matcher in Claude Code hooks is typically used to filter which events trigger the hook. For tool-related hooks (PreToolUse, PostToolUse, etc.), the matcher filters by tool name. For SessionStart, since there's no tool involved, the matcher probably just needs to be present (even as a wildcard "*") to indicate "match all session starts."

I see the configuration was incomplete. The missing matcher field likely prevented Claude Code from recognizing the hook as valid. A wildcard matcher acts as a universal trigger, ensuring the hook is always considered for execution.

